hpnicfVoCallHistory.name: hpnicfVoCallHistory

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hpnicfVoCallHistory.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of voice call history record information.

HpnicfGUid.name: HpnicfGUid
HpnicfGUid.description: Represents a global call identifier. The global call identifier is used as a unique identifier for an end-to-end call. A zero length HpnicfGUid indicates no value for the global call identifier.

hpnicfCallHistoryTable.name: hpnicfCallHistoryTable
hpnicfCallHistoryTable.description: A table containing information about specific calls to a specific destination.

hpnicfCallHistoryEntry.name: hpnicfCallHistoryEntry
hpnicfCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a single connection.

hpnicfCallHistoryIndex.name: hpnicfCallHistoryIndex
hpnicfCallHistoryIndex.description: The index of the call history table. It's a monotonically increasing integer for the sole purpose of indexing call disconnection events. When it reaches to the maximum value, the value will back to 1.

hpnicfCallHistorySetupTime.name: hpnicfCallHistorySetupTime
hpnicfCallHistorySetupTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was started.

hpnicfCallHistoryConnectTime.name: hpnicfCallHistoryConnectTime
hpnicfCallHistoryConnectTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was connected. If the call is not connected, this object will have a value of zero.

hpnicfCallHistoryTerminateTime.name: hpnicfCallHistoryTerminateTime
hpnicfCallHistoryTerminateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was terminated.

hpnicfCallHistoryPeerAddress.name: hpnicfCallHistoryPeerAddress
hpnicfCallHistoryPeerAddress.description: The number this call was connected to. If the number is not available, it will have a length of zero.

hpnicfCallHistoryPeerId.name: hpnicfCallHistoryPeerId
hpnicfCallHistoryPeerId.description: This object identifies a single peer. This is the Id value of the peer table entry to which this call was made. If a peer table entry for this call does not exist or is unknown, the value of this object will be zero.

hpnicfCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex.name: hpnicfCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex
hpnicfCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex.description: This is the ifIndex value of the logical interface through which this call was made. For ISDN media, this would be the ifIndex of the B channel which was used for this call. If the ifIndex value is unknown, the value of this object will be zero.

hpnicfCallHistoryCallOrigin.name: hpnicfCallHistoryCallOrigin
hpnicfCallHistoryCallOrigin.description: The call origin. originate The call that is initiated. answer The call that is accepted. callback Either rejects the call and then calls back, or uses the 'Reverse charging' information element if it is available. Note that callback(3) is supposed to control charging, not security, and applies to callback prior to accepting a call. Callback for security reasons can be handled using PPP callback.

hpnicfCallHistoryChargedUnits.name: hpnicfCallHistoryChargedUnits
hpnicfCallHistoryChargedUnits.description: The number of charged units for this connection. For incoming calls or if charging information is not supplied by the switch, the value of this object will be zero.

hpnicfCallHistoryInfoType.name: hpnicfCallHistoryInfoType
hpnicfCallHistoryInfoType.description: The information type for this call. other E.g. for non-isdn media. speech Speech. unrestrictedDigital Unrestricted digital information with 64k rate adaption. unrestrictedDigital56 Unrestricted digital information with 56k rate adaption. restrictedDigital Restricted digital information. audio31 3.1 kHz audio. audio7 7 kHz audio. video Video. packetSwitched Packetswitch. fax Fax.

hpnicfCallHistoryTransmitPackets.name: hpnicfCallHistoryTransmitPackets
hpnicfCallHistoryTransmitPackets.description: The number of packets which were transmitted while this call was active.

hpnicfCallHistoryTransmitBytes.name: hpnicfCallHistoryTransmitBytes
hpnicfCallHistoryTransmitBytes.description: The number of bytes which were transmitted for this call.

hpnicfCallHistoryReceivePackets.name: hpnicfCallHistoryReceivePackets
hpnicfCallHistoryReceivePackets.description: The number of packets which were received for this call.

hpnicfCallHistoryReceiveBytes.name: hpnicfCallHistoryReceiveBytes
hpnicfCallHistoryReceiveBytes.description: The number of bytes which were received for this call.

hpnicfVoiceCallHistoryTable.name: hpnicfVoiceCallHistoryTable
hpnicfVoiceCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the voice extension to the call history table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice encapsulation call leg information that is derived from the statistics of lower layer telephony interface.

hpnicfVoiceCallHistoryEntry.name: hpnicfVoiceCallHistoryEntry
hpnicfVoiceCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a extended voice call history information.

hpnicfVoCallHistoryConnectionId.name: hpnicfVoCallHistoryConnectionId
hpnicfVoCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global call identifier of circuit switched network for the gateway call.

hpnicfVoCallHistoryTxDuration.name: hpnicfVoCallHistoryTxDuration
hpnicfVoCallHistoryTxDuration.description: Duration of transmit path open from this peer to the voice gateway for the call. The units is milliseconds.

hpnicfVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration.name: hpnicfVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration
hpnicfVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration.description: Duration of voice transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The voice utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by hpnicfVoCallHistoryTxDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

hpnicfVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration.name: hpnicfVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration
hpnicfVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration.description: Duration of fax transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The fax utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by hpnicfVoCallHistoryTxDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

hpnicfVoCallHistoryCoderType.name: hpnicfVoCallHistoryCoderType
hpnicfVoCallHistoryCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the PSTN leg of a call.

hpnicfVoCallHistoryImgPageCount.name: hpnicfVoCallHistoryImgPageCount
hpnicfVoCallHistoryImgPageCount.description: The number of fax related image pages are received or transmitted via the peer for the call. The units is page.

hpnicfVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable.name: hpnicfVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable
hpnicfVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the VoIP extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains VoIP call leg information about specific VoIP call destination.

hpnicfVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry.name: hpnicfVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry
hpnicfVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a extended VoIP call history information.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global call identifier of packet-switched network for the gateway call.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType.description: The type of remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr.description: Remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort.description: Remote system UDP listener signalling port to which to transmit voice packets.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType.description: The type of remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr.description: Remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort.description: Remote system UDP listener media port to which to transmit voice packets.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol.description: The object specifies the session protocol to be used for internet call between local and remote router via IP backbone. unknown The protocol is unknown. h323 The protocol is H323. sip The protocol is session initiation.

hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType.name: hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType
hpnicfVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the VoIP leg of a call.
